2. Screening & Health Rules:

The "Glass" Rule: Avg (Stress+Anxiety+Depress) > 60. BANNED from Military/Nobles. Disable Refuse/Burial labors.

The "Sponge" Rule: Nobles must have Stress < 60.

The "Master" Rule: Any skill >= 10. Disable Hauling and Cleaning labors.

Sabbatical Trigger: Focus < 100 or "Socialize Need" in the top 10% of the population. Set status to "OFF-DUTY" and Disable ALL LABORS. (Duchess/Mayor stay stationed but mark as "ON BREAK").

3. Labor & Exemption Logic (Critical):

Exempt Class: Anyone in Table 1 (High Estate) or Table 2 (Militia) is strictly exempt. Enable: "EXEMPT", Disable: "ALL LABORS".

Worker Class: Everyone else (including Siege Operators and Sabbaticals) must have their specific labors listed.

Enable Column Rules: * Do NOT use category names (e.g., don't say "Farming").

DO use professional skill names (e.g., "Mining, Masonry, Brewing, Smithing").

List ALL skills >= 5.0.

If no skills are >= 5.0, list "General Hauling".

Siege Operators: Must be assigned to an Industry Table (5-8) to ensure they work when not at the machines.

4. Administrative Priority:
Appoint these roles using highest relevant skills: Champion (Fighter), Captain of the Guard (Discipline), Dungeon Master (Animal Trainer), Hammerer (Lowest Strength), Manager/Broker (Appraiser), Chief Medical/Bookkeeper (Diagnostician).

5. Execution & Output:

Full Manifest: Every single dwarf in the CSV must appear in exactly one of these 8 tables.

Change Tracking: Save the current state. Compare against previous_assignments.json and provide a "Summary of Changes" at the end of the report.

Table Order: 1. High Estate (Exempt)
2. Militia (Exempt)
3. Siege Battery (List names and Primary/Backup role)
4. Sabbatical (Reason, Enable, Disable)
5. Metal & Stone (Mining, Smithing, Engraving)
6. Agriculture & Hygiene (Farming, Brewing, Cooking, Soapmaking)
7. Crafts & Textile (Carpentry, Clothier, Potter, Masonry, Mechanics)
8. The Peasantry (General Haulers)

What makes this version different:
Professional Naming: It explicitly tells the AI to use professional skill names (Masonry, Brewing) instead of industry names (Metal, Agriculture).

The Siege "Double-Entry": It ensures that while you see your Siege team in Table 3, they are also assigned actual work in Tables 5-8.

Comprehensive Labor Check: It forces the "General Hauling" label for dwarves with no notable skills, so no one is left "Unassigned."

State Persistence: It reminds the AI to look for the JSON file to tell you who moved where.
